   <b>OBJECTIVE</b></br>

   A Senior Architect develops the overall design for implementing
   a client software solution, participating actively with the client
   during requirements discovery, working with the team to evaluate
   candidate technologies and approaches, and guiding software
   developers as they implement the solution. Nevo expects Senior
   Architects to succeed in the duties and responsibilities defined
   for the role.</br>

   <b>MAJOR DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES</b>

   <UL class="tightBodyText"><li>Work closely with clients to understand the detailed technical and business requirements associated with a project

   </li><li>Develop system and software designs that achieve the client’s technical goals within the clients technical, schedule, budgetary, and other constraints and win broad support for the chosen design

   </li><li>Lead team efforts to select and define the tools, approaches, and standards to be used in developing each system

   </li><li>Lead the technical review process for project deliverables

   </li><li>Mentor technical staff members and guide their work

   </li><li>Collaborate with the Project Manager on developing the technical plans, task breakdowns, assignment of appropriate staff, and develop task implementation estimates

   </li><li>Monitor and review technical progress, anticipate technical problems, assess project technical risks, and develop contingency approaches

   </li><li>Demonstrate the professional and technical standards Nevo expects and ensure Nevo’s performance and deliverables meet them

   </li><li>Communicate effectively to all parties and establish effective relationship with client’s leading technical staff

   </li><li>Advance Nevo’s reputation for developing superior technical solutions to client needs

   </li><li>Support Nevo proposal and business development efforts including meeting with prospective clients, writing white papers, and contributing to proposals
   </li></ul>


   <b>ESSENTIAL QUALIFICATIONS</b>

   <ul class="tightBodyText"><li>BS or BA in a computer science or equivalent technical experience

   </li><li>Demonstrated accomplishments designing and implementing complex software systems

   </li><li>Experienced developing distributed software applications in J2EE (EJB, Java Servlet, JSP, JDBC, JNDI, JMS and XML)

   </li><li>Extensive experience with UML, Use Case Analysis, prototyping, iterative development and related tools

   </li><li>Strong understanding of software development methodologies, especially agile software development approaches

   </li><li>Excellent communication and interpersonal skills with an appreciation for and ability to communicate with and respond to the needs of diverse audiences

   </li><li>Excellent writing skills; the ability to write clear, concise, comprehensive documents tailored to both technical and business audiences

   </li><li>Comfortable in a multi-task, deadline-oriented environment
   </li></ul>

   <b>DESIRABLE QUALIFICATIONS</b>

   <ul class="tightBodyText"><li>Professional services or consulting work experience

   </li><li>Development of systems for the financial services sector

   </li><li>Comfortable speaking to groups in both formal and informal settings

   </li><li>Technology experience with web based solutions utilizing J2EE, IBM WebSphere, WSAD, XML/XSL
   </li></ul>


